sundowner
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a swagger or itinerant who arrives at a property in the evening when work is finished, hoping for a bed.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
